@node introduction_en "Introduction"
                            AStart is @{"mailware" link legalstuff_en}!

@{b}AStart@{ub}  is  a  utility to make alternate boot-up to save memory.  It's most
important  feature is the ability to execute @{b}user-startup@{ub} incompletely.  It
will execute any @{b}IF@{ub} and @{b}LAB@{ub}el statements, allow Assign command but will not
execute  anything  else  -  this will disable the running of any patches or
commands!  You can omit this by adding @{i} ; SATETOEXECUTE @{ui} comment at the end
of   the   line   you   wish  to  be  executed  in  the  "alternate"  mode.
The   main   advantage   of   boot-up   conversion   is   that   when   you
install a program (it changes @{b}s:user-startup@{ub}), the @{b}AlternateStart@{ub} will make
the  necessary  assigns.   Usually  I had to make it manually and change it
every  time  I  installed something.  It's a pattern based comparison so to
make  it execute more or less you just have to change s:alternate-startup a
bit.   It will not run if not installed, so don't even think of testing it.
Uninstalling  is  possible  due  to  backup  of original @{b}s:startup-sequence@{ub}
(@{b}SYS:Storage/startup-sequence.bak@{ub}).   To  uninstall  it  simply restore the
startup-sequence file.

If you've got any questions or suggestions, send them to @{"me" link contact_en}.
@endnode

@node install_en "Installation"
The standard installer provides easy installation procedure.  So there's no
sense in re-writing how to use @{b}INSTALLER@{ub}.
@endnode
@node usage_en "Usage"
AStart  is  pretty  simple to use.  After installing it, simply reboot your
Amiga.   If  you  will  sold  down  shift  while  loading,  you'll  get the
AlternateStart.   If  not,  your computer will boot up normally.  Of course
the  s:startup-sequence can be still edited normally, but you must remember
not  to edit the first five lines!  If you've installed WBStartupPlus, when
you  hold  down  SHIFT  until  end of system loading, no WB program will be
launched.  This is a function of WBStartupPlus, not my patch.

If you've got any questions or suggestions, send them to @{"me" link contact_en}.
@endnode

@node legalstuff_en "Legal stuff"
This  package can be freely redistributed as long as this guide is supplied
with  it.   No  changes  should  be  made  in the guide, command (AStart or
ConvertX) or the installation script.  The package should be distributed as
an entire archive.

AStart  is  mailware!   If you use it and like it, you should send @{"me" link contact_en} a few
nice words about it.
@endnode

